version_description: In the verse, you need to strum Am right after C and F right after G, listen to the song, just like they do it. Same goes for the pre-chorus part, on "love" in "love yourself to death", just strum once and let it vibrate. The chorus is a bit harder, on Dm first strum the lower strings, then the upper strings (like if you played two separate chords), so it sounds like an octave shift. Am right after C, and at the end, strum the Am-G-F-E sequence fast, like down up down down up down down up down down up down, just like in the song, and it will sound great I promise. I'm sure you will get it, pls rate, this is my first tab, so flame as much as you like as long as it's constructive. Thanks.
